## 3. High-Level Modules

### 3.1 Public Web
Responsibilities:
- SEO pages
- calculator intake flow
- results page
- CTA / conversion actions

### 3.2 Lead & Intake Service
Responsibilities:
- capture lead info
- store uploaded files
- orchestrate parsing and simulation jobs

### 3.3 Invoice Parsing Service
Responsibilities:
- extract structured data from uploaded bills
- return field-level confidence
- support deterministic templates first
- AI fallback for unknown layouts

### 3.4 Consumption Engine
Responsibilities:
- normalize bill data
- infer annual usage and annual cost
- compute confidence score

### 3.5 Solar Simulation Engine
Responsibilities:
- estimate production per proposed configuration
- model expected yield based on location, tilt, orientation, and system sizing

### 3.6 Recommendation Engine
Responsibilities:
- choose panel count range
- select inverter candidate
- evaluate battery recommendation
- ensure compatibility with admin-managed catalog

### 3.7 Savings Engine
Responsibilities:
- estimate self-consumption
- estimate export
- estimate residual grid usage
- compute savings and break-even
- compute multiple scenarios

### 3.8 Proposal Engine
Responsibilities:
- assemble customer-facing result
- generate on-screen summary
- generate PDF proposal

### 3.9 Financing Engine
Responsibilities:
- apply financing rules
- compare cash vs financed options
- simulate early repayment assumptions

### 3.10 Tax Guidance Engine
Responsibilities:
- show current guidance content and explanatory ranges
- remain content-driven and easy to update

### 3.11 Lead Action Engine
Responsibilities:
- decide which CTAs to expose
- support call booking, email delivery, WhatsApp, reservation, contracting
- honor lead eligibility and complexity rules

### 3.12 Admin Portal
Responsibilities:
- manage catalog
- manage pricing and labor
- manage financing options
- manage tax content
- manage lead pipeline
- configure rules

