## 7. Bill Parsing Strategy

## Layer 1: Deterministic Parsing
For supported providers / layouts:
- regex / structural extraction
- table parsing if text PDF
- strong field mapping

## Layer 2: Assisted Parsing
If bill is semi-structured:
- fallback extraction rules
- confidence scoring

## Layer 3: AI Fallback
Use LLM-based structured extraction only when needed.

Important:
- never allow the LLM output to skip validation
- store extracted fields and confidence
- allow manual admin correction

---

## 8. Calculation Philosophy

## Deterministic Core
Must remain deterministic:
- annualization formulas
- catalog selection logic
- compatibility rules
- savings formulas
- financing formulas
- scenario calculations

## Generative Layer
May use AI for:
- explaining results in plain language
- summarizing proposal narrative
- parsing difficult bills as fallback

---

## 9. Recommendation Rules Strategy

Recommendation should use a rules engine, not hardcoded if/else scattered in frontend code.

Examples:
- if annual consumption > X and roof usable area >= Y, suggest range A
- if night usage high and budget allows, suggest battery option B
- if orientation poor, lower expected yield and show warning
- if aerothermal or pool present, increase demand profile weighting

Represent rules as config-driven objects where possible.

---

## 10. Savings and Financial Modeling

The financial model must separate:
- fixed power term
- variable energy term
- direct solar offset
- exported excess
- battery contribution
- residual grid consumption
- financing cost
- tax deduction scenario

The model must support:
- conservative / expected / optimistic scenarios
- versioning of assumptions

---

## 11. Security & Compliance

- protect PII and bill uploads
- limit admin access with role-based authorization
- store consent logs
- allow deletion / export flows if required
- avoid overclaiming fiscal or legal certainty

